Marubeni maintained its annual profit forecast of 230 billion yen, which was supported by pulp and paper and power generation.
Sumitomo Corporation announced on Thursday that its profit increased by 16% between April and September, emphasizing that "the trade problems between the United States and China have led to uncertain prospects."
Mitsubishi Corporation raised its annual profit forecast to a record level on Friday, due to the increase in coking coal production and the rise in commodity prices such as oil and coal.
Mitsubishi Corporation also announced a new business plan to increase its profit in the fiscal year ending March 31, 2022 from the estimated 640 billion yen this year to 900 billion yen ($7.98 billion).
