Why do people in the capital particularly love to bask in the blue sky?
Only because the people who lived in this city in the past suffered from smog and haze, they are particularly eager for the blue sky. After the "blue sky defense battle" was launched in Beijing, the air quality continued to improve, the smog became less and the blue sky increased. The people are happy in the heart, and the happiness obtained is also particularly important.
On the National Day, the weather in Beijing is fine.
At 8 o'clock in the morning, the vast majority of the 35 air quality monitoring stations in the city showed "excellent" green.
The "Blue Sky" theme photography contest initiated by the people on the social platform is still continuing.
Why is the sky so blue in Beijing recently?
According to the relevant person in charge of the Beijing Environmental Protection Bureau, in August this year, the average concentration of fine particulate matter (PM2.5) in Beijing was 35 ug / m3, setting the best record in the same period in the past five years.
In September, the real-time concentration of PM2.5 was even more frequent in single digits.
A major factor in the emergence of the "bluest sky" is that the weather conditions in recent times are generally favorable. More importantly, Beijing has continuously carried out air pollution control. In the past five years, it has vigorously promoted the clean air action plan, and the environmental benefits have continued to be released. The total amount of pollutants in the region has been reduced, which has laid the foundation for continuous improvement of air quality.
Beijing officially released and implemented the "Beijing Clean Air Action Plan 2013-2017" in 2013.
According to the plan, officials continue to guide non-capital functions, promote energy clean substitution and pollution reduction, and eliminate 4,923 coal-fired boilers.
Beijing has thus become the first major city in mainland China to realize the natural gas of the whole network.
According to the data, between 2013 and 2017, the average annual concentration of PM2.5 in Beijing decreased by 35.6%; the number of days of air quality compliance increased by 50 days; the number of days of first-class excellent increased by 25 days; the number of days of heavy pollution decreased by 35 days, and the incidence of heavy pollution decreased significantly.
While the air quality continues to improve, Beijing officials released the "Three-Year Action Plan for Beijing to Win the Blue Sky Defense Battle" in September this year, focusing on the key prevention and control areas such as diesel trucks, dust, and volatile organic compounds, optimizing and adjusting the transportation structure, industrial structure, energy structure and land structure, strengthening the regional joint control, and striving to strengthen the city's green development.
