The reporter learned from the Ministry of Finance on the 30th that the Ministry of Finance, the State Administration of Taxation, the National Development and Reform Commission, and the Ministry of Commerce jointly issued a notice recently. In order to further encourage foreign investors to invest in China, the profits distributed by foreign investors from Chinese domestic resident enterprises will be used for domestic direct investment. The scope of application of the withholding income tax policy is temporarily expanded from foreign investment incentive projects to all non-prohibited foreign investment projects and fields.
This policy will be implemented from January 1, 2018.
The circular makes it clear that the direct investment made by foreign investors with the share of profits includes the equity investment behaviors such as capital increase, new construction and equity acquisition made by foreign investors with the share of profits, but does not include the addition, transfer and acquisition of listed companies in addition to eligible strategic investments.
If an overseas investor can enjoy the policy of temporarily withholding income tax but does not actually enjoy it, he may apply for the recovery of the policy within three years from the date of actual payment of the relevant tax, and refund the tax paid.
Not only that, after foreign investors enjoy the prescribed temporary non-collection of withholding income tax policy treatment, the invested enterprise reorganizes in line with the special reorganization conditions, and actually conducts tax treatment according to the special reorganization, and can continue to enjoy the temporary non-collection of withholding income tax policy treatment.
In order to ensure that the profits earned by foreign investors are actually used for direct investment, the notice stipulates that if the profits used by foreign investors for direct investment are paid in cash, the relevant funds are directly transferred from the account of the profit distribution enterprise to the account of the invested enterprise or the equity transferor. Before the direct investment, it may not be transferred to other accounts at home and abroad; if the profits used by foreign investors for direct investment are paid in non-cash forms such as physical, marketable securities, etc., the ownership of the relevant assets is directly transferred from the profit distribution enterprise or the equity transfer party, and the relevant assets are not directly held by the investment enterprise or other individuals before the direct investment.
The circular also requires the tax department to strengthen follow-up management according to law.
Overseas investors have enjoyed the policy of not collecting pre-paid income tax for the time being. If the tax department's follow-up management verifies that it does not meet the prescribed conditions, in addition to the corporate responsibility for profit distribution, it is considered that overseas investors have not declared and paid enterprise income tax in accordance with the regulations, and the tax delay will be investigated according to law. The tax payment period is calculated from the date of the relevant profit payment.
