Xinhua News Agency, Fuzhou, October 1 (Reporter Yu Xiaoan) On October 1, the "Regulations on the Safety Management of Fujian High-speed Railway" was officially implemented.
The regulations propose that within 500 meters on both sides of the high-speed rail power line, it is forbidden to fly kites, balloons, Kong Ming lanterns, aircraft and other airborne objects and small aircraft.
It is stipulated that on the basis of the "Railway Law of the People's Republic of China" and the "Regulations on the Administration of Railway Safety," according to the geographical and climatic characteristics of Fujian Province, the prohibition and restriction of high-speed rail safety will be supplemented, and the construction and tree planting along the high-speed rail will be standardized. Further clarify the main body of high-speed rail supervision and the scope of supervision, and clarify the duties and legal responsibilities of law enforcement supervision.
The regulations stipulate that in view of the high winds in the coastal areas of Fujian Province, the light construction materials and light objects along the high-speed rail are blown into the high-speed rail to affect the safety of the high-speed rail, and the high-speed rail power line wires are within 500 meters on both sides of the high-speed rail line. It is forbidden to fly kites, balloons, Kongming lights, power umbrellas, aircraft and other airborne objects and small aircraft.
In addition, light objects such as plastic greenhouses, colored steel plates, and sunshade nets along the high-speed rail line and light objects such as low-altitude floats and plastic protective films generated during the construction process, the owner or user should take reinforcement and protection measures to prevent high-speed railway safety.
In view of the fact that Fujian Province is in a hilly area and there are many high-speed railway tunnels, the regulations require that the construction of Shantang, reservoir, dam, excavation of river channels, dry canals, drilling wells, etc. may affect the safety of tunnels within 200 meters on both sides of the central line above the high-speed railway tunnel, and should seek the opinions of railway construction units or railway transportation enterprises.
At the same time, those who violate the relevant responsibilities of the "Regulations" will be ordered by the public security organs to correct; if the circumstances are serious, the unit will be fined not less than 5,000 yuan and not more than 10,000 yuan, and the individual will be fined not less than 200 yuan and not more than 500 yuan; if the circumstances are serious, the unit will be fined not less than 10,000 yuan, and the individual will be fined not more than 500 yuan and not more than 1,000 yuan.
If losses are caused, they shall be liable for compensation according to law.
It is understood that with the rapid development of railway construction, the high-speed railway mileage of 200 kilometers per hour and above in Fujian Province has reached 1516 kilometers, and the city has achieved a train. It is expected that the railway line of 200 kilometers per hour and above in Fujian will reach 2150 kilometers in the next five years.
The implementation of the regulations will standardize the safety management of high-speed rail in Fujian Province, further implement the duties of local government departments, coordinate railways and local forces, work together to ensure the safety of high-speed rail, and improve the safety prevention and control system of high-speed rail in Fujian Province.
