Indonesia strong earthquake tsunami disaster devastated the number of victims or as many as thousands - Zhongxin
According to comprehensive reports, a shallow earthquake of magnitude 7.5 occurred on the Indonesian island of Sulawesi on September 28, triggering a 6-meter-high tsunami.
The national disaster response department announced on September 30 that the death toll increased to 832, mainly concentrated in the capital Palu and Donggara County near the epicenter.
Vice President Kara pointed out that since some disaster areas have not yet calculated the number of casualties, the number of deaths may be as many as thousands.
The strong earthquake and tsunami that occurred on the afternoon of September 28 in Indonesia's Central Sulawesi Province have killed 832 people.
Thousands of buildings collapsed and 2.4 million people were affected
After the Palu disaster, thousands of buildings collapsed and many roads were broken. The authorities said that about 2.4 million people were affected.
A hotel on the local coast collapsed. Only 24 guests escaped safely. It is estimated that about 50 to 60 people were trapped in the rubble. The scene was heard from time to time. Rescuers successfully rescued a young woman on September 30.
Due to the safety of the trapped people, the authorities were unable to use heavy machines to remove the rubble, and the search and rescue progress was slow.
A shopping mall in the city also collapsed, and hundreds of residents rushed to the scene, waiting for the news of friends and relatives.
Many residents use social platforms to send letters to find separated friends and relatives.
On September 30th, local time, a hotel collapsed in Balu City, Central Sulawesi, Indonesia, and rescue work was launched.
Palu 10,000 people to be rescued 5 foreigners unaccounted for
Authorities said that there are about 10,000 people waiting for rescue in Palu, scattered in 50 locations.
It is reported that 71 foreigners were in Palu at the time of the earthquake. For the time being, 66 of them are known to be safe, including 21 Chinese citizens. The remaining two French, two Malaysian tourists and one Korean are unaccounted for.
The Chinese Embassy in Indonesia is checking the status of Chinese citizens in the disaster area through various channels, and has not received reports of casualties among Chinese citizens.
Communication in Donggara County, near the epicentre of the earthquake, was still interrupted. It was temporarily learned that 11 people were killed, but there was no more detailed information.
According to the scene, the coastal areas and ports of Donggara County were severely damaged, a large number of buildings were swept away, bodies were scattered everywhere, and the Red Cross rescue team was going to the local search and rescue.
Indonesian president inspects disaster situation and says reconstruction work will begin as soon as possible
The roads in Palu and Donggara were severely damaged. On September 30, Palu Airport only opened the use of aircraft carrying relief materials, allowing relief materials and personnel to arrive as soon as possible and remove the seriously injured.
Many local hospitals are still without power, and the injured have to be treated outdoors.
More than 10,000 victims stayed in the reception center. Some people worried that aftershocks did not dare to go home, preferring to spend the night outdoors.
After the collapse of a prison in Palu in the earthquake, causing hundreds of prisoners to escape from prison, more than 100 prisoners in Donggara County took advantage of the chaos caused by the earthquake, and some prisoners set fire to the detention center.
Indonesian President Joko visited Palu on September 30 to inspect the disaster. He pointed out that it is very difficult to solve a large number of problems in a short period of time, including restoring communications.
He appealed to the victims to be patient and said that the authorities would start the reconstruction work as soon as possible.
On the other hand, the Indonesian Finance Minister announced that the government has allocated 560 billion Indonesian rupiah for disaster relief.
A human case of H5N6 avian influenza confirmed in Guangdong Province
The Health Bureau said that according to the latest report from the mainland health department, a case of H5N6 avian influenza was confirmed in Guangdong Province.
The Health Bureau appealed to residents to avoid contact with birds and pay attention to personal and food hygiene.
According to the data, the patient is a 22-year-old man who now lives in Baiyun District, Guangzhou City, Guangdong Province. He developed fever and other symptoms on September 25 and was admitted to hospital on September 26. He is currently in isolation in the hospital and is in critical condition.
The patient had slaughtered and eaten live poultry before the onset of the disease.
Since April 2014, there have been confirmed cases of H5N6 avian influenza in Sichuan, Guangdong, Yunnan, Hubei, Hunan, Anhui and Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region.
The Health Bureau will continue to maintain close contact with the health departments of the country and neighboring areas and the World Health Organization to closely monitor the epidemic situation in various places and in Australia.
To prevent human infection with avian influenza, the Health Bureau urges the public to pay attention to the following matters:
Avoid contact with birds or their secretions and excreta; if there is contact, wash hands immediately;
Do not buy or carry birds that have not been quarantined;
Do not eat poultry meat, internal organs, blood products and eggs that have not been thoroughly cooked;
Pay attention to personal hygiene and wash hands often;
If you have symptoms such as fever, cough, and breathing difficulties, you should wear a mask, seek medical treatment as soon as possible, and detail the travel history and animal contact history to the doctor.
