The Beijing News (Reporter Ni Wei) The State Administration of Radio, Film and Television issued the "Notice on Carrying out the Special Work of Radio and Television Advertising" on September 29, and launched the special rectification work of radio and television advertising from now until the end of this year.
The rectification content includes advertisements with vulgar content, low style and low grade, and medical health programs that broadcast problems without record management.
According to the notice, the special rectification work focuses on nine aspects to find and rectify.
Specifically, it includes: advertisements with guiding problems; advertisements with vulgar content, low style and low grade; advertisements with overtime and excessive quantity, and advertisements that do not broadcast according to regulations; there are exaggerated and exaggerated false propaganda, misleading audiences, or medical treatment, medical equipment, health food, cosmetics, beauty, etc., there are problems such as medical advertisements that have not been broadcast without record management; there are problems such as medical health care programs that do not exaggerate, mislead, mislead, mislead, mislead, etc.
The rectification work will be fully covered throughout the country, and the requirements for rectification and standardization will be fully implemented to all levels of radio and television media, channel frequencies, program columns and time periods. "No blind spots, no dead corners, no exceptions."
The circular requires that the administrative departments of radio and television at all levels should deal with all kinds of illegal and illegal advertisements found in the supervision and inspection in strict accordance with the "Measures for Handling Violations of Radio and Television Broadcasting Institutions" of the General Administration.
If the violation is serious, it is necessary to give serious treatment such as talking, criticizing, suspending advertising broadcast until suspending the frequency channel broadcast, and publicly exposing it to the public as appropriate.
In recent years, the State Administration of Radio, Film and Television has repeatedly stopped illegal advertisements.
This year, the State Administration of Radio and Television issued a notice to publicly stop the advertisements of "0 bubble fruit milk," "Shawa cocktail" and "Bonritt plant anti-debreeding and revealing" and other serious violations such as exaggerating and exaggerating propaganda and misleading the audience.
The State Administration of Radio, Film and Television has formulated a number of laws and regulations and circulars to regulate the behavior of radio and television advertisements.
"Notice on Further Strengthening the Advertising Management of TV Shopping Short Films on TV Channel" stipulates that TV shopping short advertisements may not be broadcast during the period from 18: 00 to 24: 00 every day.
When broadcasting TV shopping short film advertisements in other periods, the host shall not be used for propaganda, and the "hawking type" exaggerated dubbing, intonation, action, etc., shall not use "orthopedic," "plastic," "fat" and "fat" propaganda or disguised promotion of breast enhancement and weight loss products. The TV shopping short film advertisements must not exceed 1 (time) every hour, and each time must not exceed 3 minutes.
"Notice on Further Strengthening the Broadcasting Management of Radio and Television Advertisements" stipulates that when TV stations insert advertisements in the middle of film and television dramas, they must strictly abide by the provisions of the General Administration's Order No. 61: non-prime time can be inserted 2 commercial advertisements in each episode (45 minutes), each time must not exceed 1 minute and 30 seconds; prime time (19: 00 to 21: 00) can be inserted 1 commercial advertisement in each episode, and the duration should not exceed 1 minute.
The circular also stipulates that radio and television broadcasting institutions should strictly examine the qualifications and certificates of health information advertisements such as medical treatment, medicines, medical devices, health food, etc., and resolutely prohibit the broadcast of sex-related advertisements.
To standardize the form of health information advertisements, advertisements should not be published in disguised form in the form of health information special programs.
The special program of health information shall focus on introducing scientific knowledge such as disease prevention, control and treatment, and shall not contain advertisements such as medical treatment, medicines, medical devices, health foods, etc., and shall not be certified in the name of patients and doctors, pharmacists, experts, etc.
