Yichang, October 1, ZXS (Guo Xiaoying Liu Min) The newly revised "Three Gorges-Gezhouba Water Conservancy Project Navigation and Dispatching Regulations" (hereinafter referred to as "Dispatching Regulations") officially began to be implemented on October 1. After two years of trial navigation, the Three Gorges ship lift was officially unified with the ship lock.
On the first day of the implementation of the new regulations, the navigation order of the Three Gorges-Gezhouba waters was good.
The Yangtze River Three Gorges Navigation Administration issued the first security check plan at 21: 00 on September 30, and conducted security checks on 160 ships. A total of 124 ships passed the security check.
At 1400 hours on October 1, the navigation department arranged the first crossing plan after the implementation of the new regulations.
After the implementation of the new regulations, the security plan will be issued at 9: 00 and 21: 00 every day, and the dam plan will be issued at 14: 00 and 20: 00 every day, so that the ship can flexibly arrange the dam plan.
The "Dispatching Regulations" adds the principle of "classification control" for the ship's dam-crossing dispatching. According to the functional positioning of the ship lock and the ship lifter, the priority order of the ship crossing the dam is clearly defined, and the short-term passenger ship that passes the gate is adjusted to the same priority level as the demonstration ship and the integrity ship.
This is also the second anniversary of the trial operation of the ship lift, officially and the ship lock unified dispatching.
And the Chuanjiang River and the Three Gorges reservoir area big long and wide demonstration ship, the new energy power ship also entered the priority level for the first time.
At the same time, the "Dispatching Regulations" will adjust the "navigable dispatching management waters" from the previous 180 kilometers near the dam waters to the Yunyang Yangtze River Bridge to the Shishou Yangtze River Bridge 541.8 kilometers of waters, and divide the "core waters, near the dam waters, control waters, dispatching waters."
This is conducive to the shipowner to choose suitable waters to be locked and reduce the backlog of ships to be locked in the dam area.
According to the characteristics of the current ship crossing the dam and waiting for the gate, the "Dispatching Regulations" also puts forward the integrity control measures such as the cancellation declaration of the offending ship and the 24-hour delay in crossing the dam.
After the Three Gorges water storage, the navigation conditions in the reservoir area have been improved, which promotes the rapid development of the Yangtze River shipping.
According to the data, the annual cargo throughput of the Three Gorges Shiplock and Gezhouba Shiplock increased from 34.3 million tons in 2004 to 138 million tons and 140 million tons in 2017.
Three Gorges ship lift test navigation in the past two years through the ship 5767 times, 162.2 million passengers, cargo volume of 171.28 million tons.
Chen Dongyuan, deputy director of the Three Gorges Navigation Administration, said that the "Dispatching Regulations" has a positive effect on promoting the management of the two dams, maintaining the navigation order of the two dams, relieving the pressure of the ships in the dam area, and improving the navigation capacity.
