Inner Mongolia import and export links 46 kinds of supervision certificates all realize network verification - Zhongxin
Hohhot, November 5 (Reporter Li Aiping) Hohhot Customs said on the 5th that from now on, in addition to special circumstances such as confidentiality needs, all 46 kinds of supervision certificates in the local import and export links will be networked for verification.
Inner Mongolia enterprises can use paperless way to declare relevant documents to the customs, avoiding problems such as on-site running, paper application, and repeated submission.
It is understood that the document preparation time refers to the preparation time of all kinds of documents required for the import and export link before the declaration of customs declaration. It is a major factor affecting the overall customs clearance time. If you want to compress the customs clearance time and reduce the customs clearance cost, you must reduce the document.
Previously, there were 86 kinds of regulatory documents that required customs inspection in the import and export links, involving 19 departments.
It is reported that this time, in accordance with the principle of "cancellation that can be cancelled, merger that can be merged, and exit the exit port inspection that can be withdrawn from the port inspection," relying on the international trade "single window" platform, the customs and other 16 certification authorities system docking and data interconnection, achieving more data runs and less errands for enterprises.
Customs said that in the past, enterprises need to go back and forth to the relevant departments to submit paper applications in the on-site office hall, and the process is long and cannot track the status of the audit in real time.
Now enterprise users can directly log in to the "single window" portal website to apply online.
After the approval of the certification department, the certificate electronic data transmission to the customs, and in the customs clearance link to achieve automatic comparison with the customs declaration data, intelligent verification, the audit results are uniformly fed back to the enterprise through the "single window," and the supervision certificate declaration, audit, customs clearance and feedback are processed online.
Korean ginseng chicken soup exports to China soared 20 times in 4 years or related to the increase of empty nest youth - Zhongxin
The export of Korean ginseng chicken soup to China has soared 20 times in 4 years: related to the increase of empty nest youth
Yonhap reported on the 5th that the export value of Korean ginseng chicken soup to China exceeded 100,000 US dollars last year, which was about 20 times higher than that of 2013 four years ago.
According to the analysis, this increase is related to the increase of China's empty nest youth to promote convenient food sales, as well as the increase of young people's attention to nutritious meals.
The data was released by the Korean Agricultural and Aquatic Food Circulation Commune (aT) on the 5th.
Last year, the export value of Korean ginseng chicken soup to China reached 100.339 million US dollars, weighing 218.59 million kilograms, which increased by 2094% and 3668.8% respectively compared with 2013.
According to the analysis, the increase in sales of Korean ginseng chicken soup in China is related to the increase in the number of empty nests and the promotion of convenient food sales, as well as the attention of young people to nutritious meals.
As of this year, China's one-person households have exceeded the 200 million mark. It is expected to increase to 30% of the total population in 2020. Local food companies have also targeted the "single-family" to launch various convenient foods.
In addition, the analysis also said that avian influenza is the biggest factor that prevents ginseng chicken soup from taking root in the Chinese mainland market.
aT said that from November 2016 to April last year, there was an outbreak of avian influenza in South Korea. The relevant departments completely banned the export of ginseng chicken soup to China, resulting in a sharp drop in exports.
In 2016, the export value of ginseng chicken soup to China reached 840,000 US dollars. Due to avian influenza, the export value plummeted to 100,000 US dollars last year.
