The newly revised Personal Income Tax Law adjusts the judgment standard of China's personal income tax residents from one year to 183 days.
The relevant person in charge of the Ministry of Finance and the State Administration of Taxation said on the 30th that in order to maintain policy stability, the next step in implementing the new personal income tax law will consider continuing to make preferential arrangements for overseas people, including Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan.
The person in charge said that the current regulations on the implementation of the Individual Income Tax Law have special preferential provisions on the taxation of overseas people. Individuals who have no residence in China but live for more than one year and less than five years may only pay personal income tax on the part paid by units or individuals in China.
The part paid abroad does not need to pay personal income tax within China.
The Ministry of Finance, the State Administration of Taxation, the National Development and Reform Commission, and the Ministry of Commerce also issued a notice to expand the scope of application of the withholding income tax policy for foreign investors to distribute profits.
The scope of application of the policy of withholding income tax for domestic direct investment is temporarily not levied on the profits distributed by foreign investors from domestic resident enterprises, and the projects of encouraging foreign investment are expanded to all projects and fields that are not prohibited from foreign investment.
During the 73rd session of the United Nations General Assembly, the parties released some positive messages on the Korean Peninsula issue.
South Korean President Moon Jae-yin relayed the "irreversible" nuclear abandonment determination of the DPRK and said that US President Trump and North Korea's supreme leader Kim Jong-un may meet before the end of this year.
The US State Department later said that Secretary of State Pompeo will visit North Korea in October to promote the implementation of the US-DPRK leaders' Singapore meeting commitments.
Since the beginning of this year, the two Koreas have broken the ice to open the road of dialogue, the leaders of the two Koreas and the DPRK and the United States have held meetings, the general trend of easing the situation on the peninsula has continued, and the principle of dialogue to resolve the peninsula issue has been adhered to.
First of all, the "essence of the peninsula issue is a security issue" has not changed. The key to achieving peace on the peninsula is to properly and balance the reasonable security concerns of all parties, rather than blindly pressuring each other and emphasizing their own demands.
Secondly, in the dialogue on realizing the denuclearization of the peninsula, the parties concerned still disagree on the steps and ways to realize the denuclearization of the peninsula. Due to the long-term lack of political trust between the DPRK and the United States, the game thinking of "who is first and who is later" is still strong.
Recently, at the open meeting of the Security Council on the Korean Peninsula held at the United Nations Headquarters in New York, the different voices of the parties on the issue of sanctions against the DPRK once again highlighted the "no change" on the peninsula issue.
US Secretary of State Pompeo insisted that sanctions against North Korea will not be lifted until the Korean Peninsula is completely denuclearized.
Russian Foreign Minister Sergei Lavrov stressed the principle of "responding to action with action," pointing out: "The weakening trend of sanctions should be the same as the steps taken by North Korea on the road of gradually abandoning nuclear weapons."
There is no doubt that all parties concerned should continue to implement the Security Council resolutions related to the DPRK in a comprehensive, complete and accurate manner, but pressure is not the end. The implementation of sanctions and the promotion of political settlement are the requirements of the Security Council resolutions.
As Chinese State Councilor and Foreign Minister Wang Yi said, in view of the current positive progress in inter-Korean and DPRK-US relations, China believes that it is necessary for the Security Council to consider timely launching reversible clauses, thus encouraging North Korea and relevant parties to take greater steps toward denuclearization.
Looking back on the past, the denuclearization of the peninsula and every progress in the peace process require all parties to show sufficient political courage.
At present, in the face of the growing expectations of the international community to promote a political solution to the peninsula issue, all parties concerned should show political courage, make political decisions, implement commitments, resolve difficult problems, continue to take steps to meet each other, and promote the denuclearization process of the peninsula and establish a peace mechanism on the peninsula. Work together to create a permanent peace on the peninsula.
