Oil prices or ushered in the "three consecutive rises" National Day self-driving travel can be filled with oil in advance.
BEIJING, September 30 (Reporter Qiu Yu) At 24: 00 on September 30, a new round of refined oil price adjustment window will be opened simultaneously with the National Day holiday.
A number of institutions predict that oil prices will be significantly raised to achieve "three consecutive increases."
Owners who plan to travel by self-driving can fill their cars with oil before the price increase.
According to the data calculated by Longzhong Information, it is estimated that the corresponding increase of domestic refined oil products is about 190 yuan / ton; the increase of Zhuochuang Information is 220 yuan / ton.
In September, the oil price has been raised twice: on September 3, the gasoline was raised by 180 yuan / ton, and the diesel oil was raised by 170 yuan / ton; on September 17, the gasoline was raised by 145 yuan / ton, and the diesel was raised by 145 yuan / ton.
Domestic oil prices are linked to international oil prices. Since the current pricing cycle, international oil prices have risen, and Brent crude oil has broken through the $80 mark and continued to rise.
By the close of trading on September 28, US WTI crude oil futures closed up $1.13 at $73.25 per barrel.
Brent crude oil futures closed up $1.0 at $82.72 per barrel.
"From the international situation, the United States sanctions Iran and other tensions superimposed, the overall trend of oil prices is strong, and then the OPEC production reduction meeting clearly refused to increase production, giving market confidence, and oil prices steadily moved up."
Zhuochuang information refined oil analyst Zang Wengang said.
In terms of retail, the current gasoline prices of No. 92 and No. 95 of Beijing PetroChina and Sinopec gas stations are 7.66 yuan / liter and 8.15 yuan / liter respectively.
According to Li Yan, an information analyst at Longzhong, the retail sales promotion strategy of the gas station has not changed much. At present, the preferential margin of Sinopec and other main stations is more than 0.5-0.7 yuan / liter, while the preferential margin of private gas stations is more than 0.5-1.2 yuan / liter.
