Despite the continued turmoil in the global financial market, the Hong Kong Monetary Authority said on Monday that the investment income of the Exchange Fund in the third quarter of this year decreased by 97% year-on-year, but it was better than the performance of the previous quarter. Due to the Sino-US trade war, overseas stocks rose and foreign exchange losses narrowed significantly.
According to the latest data of the HKMA, the Exchange Fund recorded investment income of HK $1.6 billion in July-September 2018, which was significantly lower than the HK $61.8 billion in the same period last year, but better than the revised HK $100 million in the second quarter of this year.
Chen Delin, president of the HKMA, said in the Legislative Council that at the beginning of the Sino-US trade war, the Hong Kong and emerging market stock indexes ran counter to the US stock index. After the US stock market index peaked in late September and early October, market sentiment began to reverse, as investors gradually realized that the trade war was also detrimental to the United States itself.
"It is a good thing that market sentiment has changed. If the trade war has only one-sided influence, it will not help to solve things."
But he also pointed out that "if the Sino-US trade war is not resolved, financial market volatility will continue to rise."
In the third quarter of this year, the stock investment loss of the Exchange Fund in Hong Kong narrowed by 8% to HK $4.7 billion compared with the previous quarter, while the investment income of overseas stocks increased by 172% to HK $12.8 billion; the foreign exchange loss was HK $16.2 billion, and the bond income was HK $9.7 billion, which decreased by 24% and 31% respectively. Mainly reflects the general increase of the US dollar against major currencies during the quarter and the US interest rate rose by 3% in mid-September.
The Exchange Fund is mainly used to support the Hong Kong dollar.
Hong Kong has implemented the linked exchange rate system of the Hong Kong dollar and the US dollar since 1983.
Regarding the current financial situation in Hong Kong, Chen Delin said that the economic and asset market uncertainty has increased and the downside risks have increased, but the Hong Kong financial system is stable, and it is also well defended, and the seismic capacity is abundant.
"Hong Kong's international investment position is abundant. The external net asset value is 1.4 trillion US dollars equivalent to 4 times GDP, which is higher than 2.5 times that of Singapore and 0.6 times that of Japan. It is more than enough to cope with the economic downturn or reversal."
Recently, the Hong Kong dollar interest rate continued to fall and the spread with the US dollar expanded. Chen Delin pointed out that the Hong Kong dollar exchange rate rose by more than 400 basis points on September 21. The market is generally believed to be mainly related to the rise of the Hong Kong dollar interest rate. After that, the Hong Kong dollar has hovered around 7.80-7.84.
However, he believes that with the beginning of the interest rate hike cycle of Hong Kong banks and the normalization of Hong Kong dollar interest rates, the future situation of Hong Kong dollar interest rates below US dollar interest rates will change.
"The trend of Hong Kong dollar interest rates and US dollar interest rates will be more consistent. Everyone must be more careful to manage risks and be prepared to cope with market fluctuations."
As the Hong Kong dollar funds were very abundant, the Hong Kong dollar interest rate fell further. The three-month interest rate fell by 0.9% to 2.08179% on Monday, and the spread with the US dollar expanded from 46 basis points to 51 basis points; the one-month interest rate hit a five-month low, and the spread with the US dollar expanded from 120 basis points to 127 basis points.
From May to mid-September, the spot exchange rate of the Hong Kong dollar was close to 7.85 to the US dollar for most of the time.
During the period, due to factors such as the outflow of some funds from the IPO after the completion of the arbitrage activities and large-scale prospectus activities, the weak party exchange guarantee was triggered several times in May and August after it was triggered for the first time in April.
The HKMA buys Hong Kong dollars and sells US dollars at the 7.85 level in accordance with the linked exchange rate system to maintain the stability of the Hong Kong dollar exchange rate.
The HKMA bought about HK $52.1 billion under the weak exchange guarantee mechanism in May and August.
