Macron promotes France to protect French skills for the "baguette" heritage - Zhongxin
BEIJING, Oct. 1, according to Reuters, European countries have successively applied for their own unique diets. Following the Belgian beer and the pancakes in Naples, Italy, France recently plans to apply for long-stick bread, which is included in the UNESCO Intangible Cultural Heritage List.
It is reported that the plan was promoted by French President Macron, and the French Bread and Pastry Industry Alliance expressed support.
They pointed out that many of the baguettes currently sold are made from large-scale frozen dough, adding materials other than flour, water, yeast and salt. The traditional handmade bakery is gradually declining, hoping to be included in the list to protect the world-renowned French skills.
UNESCO will hold its annual meeting in Mauritius in late November to review the Intangible Cultural Heritage List.
Five people were killed when an illegal migrant boat sank off the Aegean Sea in Turkey.
Istanbul, 30 Sep (Xinhua) -- According to Turkish media reports on the 30th, an inflatable boat carrying illegal immigrants capsized in the Aegean Sea of Turkey on the same day, killing at least five people.
Reported that the inflatable boat scheduled to travel to a Greek island sank near the Enez area of Edirne Province in northwestern Turkey on the same day. The cause of the sinking is unknown.
At present, it is not clear the number of illegal immigrants on the sinking inflatable boat.
Because it is estimated that there are still people trapped in the sea, the relevant search and rescue operations are still continuing.
The Aegean Sea was once the preferred route for illegal immigrants to smuggle to the European continent through Turkey.
After Turkey controlled it under the agreement signed with the EU in March 2016, the number of people smuggled through this channel was greatly reduced.
But so far this year, the number of people smuggling on this channel has rebounded.
