In recent years, there have been many incidents of unqualified campus plastic runways.
To this end, the Ministry of Education issued a notice requiring the implementation of the new national standard for the surface layer of synthetic materials for primary and secondary schools delivered after November 1 this year.
Mandatory national standard "primary and secondary school synthetic materials surface sports ground" led by the Ministry of Education, 26 scientific research institutes and testing institutions participated in the drafting. After more than two years of revision, more than 100 expert meetings were organized during the period, as well as nationwide field visits and sampling inspections. Countless verification experiments of hundreds of enterprise products on the market.
The reporter compared the old national standard in 2005 and found that the new national standard not only changed from "national recommended standard" to "national mandatory standard," but also added many contents, including thickness requirements, physical performance, anti-aging performance, inorganic filler content requirements, anti-skid rubber polymer content requirements, surface finished products. Limit of harmful substances, non-solid and solid raw materials, etc.
In particular, the new national standard has limited the harmful substances that may be produced in the construction of the campus plastic runway, from the original 7 items to 18 items, and has made regulations on the volatile organic compounds of the runway after completion according to the home decoration standards.
Such as "cast-in-place and prefabricated surface finished products in the limit of harmful substances and odor requirements" clearly stipulates the release of harmful substances, requiring that the total volatile organic compounds should not be higher than 5 mg / m3, formaldehyde should not be higher than 0.4 mg / m3, carbon disulfide should not be higher than 7 mg / m3, benzene should not be higher than 0.1 mg / m3, and the smell level should not be higher than 3.
The new national standard also makes detailed regulations on the sampling requirements, inspection rules, and judgment rules of the plastic runway on the campus of primary and secondary schools.
In addition, the campus artificial lawn is also included in the scope of compulsory testing of the national standard for the first time.
In the near future, all localities should carry out special work arrangements for the implementation of the new national standard, and submit the implementation of the new national standard to the Sports Health and Art Education Department of the Ministry of Education during the year.
