From November 1st, China will reduce the MFN tax rate for some commodities, and the total tariff level will be reduced to 7.5%.
According to the decision of the 26th executive meeting of the State Council, the Customs Tariff Commission of the State Council issued a notice on the 30th, and from November 1, 2018, the MFN tax rate of some commodities will be reduced.
According to the "Notice of the Customs Tariff Commission of the State Council on Reducing the Import Tariff of Some Commodities," in order to adapt to industrial upgrading, reduce enterprise costs and meet the needs of the masses for multi-level consumption, from November 1 this year, the MFN tax rate for some industrial products and other commodities will be reduced.
There are 1,585 tax items for tax reduction commodities, accounting for about 19% of the total number of tax items in China. The average tax rate dropped from 10.5% to 7.8%, and the average decline was 26%.
This tax reduction mainly involves textiles; stone, ceramics, glass products; some steel and base metal products; mechanical and electrical equipment and parts, such as metal processing machinery, textile machinery, construction machinery, transmission and transformation equipment, electrical equipment, instrumentation, etc.; resource commodities and primary processing products, such as non-metal mines, inorganic chemicals, wood and paper products, precious jade, etc.
At the same time, with the reduction of the total tariff level, especially the import tariffs on medicines and consumer goods, the tax rate of import duties on imported goods will be lowered accordingly.
In order to implement the decision and deployment of the Party Central Committee and the State Council, China has implemented zero tariffs on the vast majority of imported drugs since May 1 this year. From July 1, the import tariffs on automobiles and parts and some consumer goods have been reduced, and the information technology agreement has been implemented. The third step of expanding products is to reduce taxes.
The reporter learned from the Customs Tariff Commission of the State Council that since the beginning of this year, after continuous independent adjustments, China's total tariff level will drop from 9.8% in the previous year to 7.5%, with an average decline of 23%.
The appropriate reduction of tariffs is conducive to promoting the balanced development of foreign trade and promoting a higher level of opening up to the outside world. It is also conducive to the overall use of international and domestic resources and promoting domestic supply-side structural reforms.
The relevant person in charge of the committee said that this year is the 40th anniversary of reform and opening up. The initiative to reduce the overall level of tariffs is a practical action to implement the spirit of General Secretary Xi Jinping's important speech at the Boao Forum for Asia. It is also an important measure for China to further expand opening up and actively expand imports in accordance with its own high-quality development needs. This action and initiative show that China will unswervingly pursue a mutually beneficial and win-win opening strategy, while enhancing its own development momentum, it also allows China to better benefit the world.
On September 29th, the regional public brand conference of "Huanxiang People" agricultural products in Huanxian County, Gansu Province was held in Nankai District of Tianjin.
Red Army Xiaomi, black beans, mountain children's songs black goats, hardcover bitter tea, paper-cut shadow books, pure handmade slippers... A piece of beautifully packaged agricultural products is neatly placed on the booth. They have a common brand name called "Huanxiang People."
"Building the regional brand of" Huanxiang People "has effectively solved the bottleneck of the development of Huanxian's agricultural products, which is scattered, small and weak, and has become a powerful carrier for poverty alleviation." On the 29th, the "Huanxiang People" agricultural products regional public brand conference was held in Nankai District, Tianjin.
Huanxian is located at the junction of the three provinces of Shaanxi, Gansu and Ningxia. As a "national grain production advanced county," "China's small grain town" and "China's shadow town," it has a long history and abundant resources.
Lamb meat, yellow rice wine, chop noodles, swallow noodles soft and other local snacks are often remembered by tourists in other countries.
With the continuous improvement of China's urbanization level and the rapid increase of urban population, a large number of rural young people leave their hometown to start urban life.
Yang Qiaojia, an expert in China's agricultural brand research, said: "Now urban life is fast and stressful. More and more people are beginning to miss the rural life as a child. However, the most beautiful memory is the countryside. The brand design is named after the nostalgia and nostalgia of the people who are drifting around the county."
Huanxian has special climatic conditions, long sunshine time, large temperature difference between day and night, and unique planting conditions for small grains.
The territory is rich in more than 20 kinds of small grains. It is the hometown of small grains in China. The output ranks first in Gansu, and the quality is in the forefront of the country.
Wang Xiaoli is a Huanxian girl who went to school in Tianjin. This time, she participated in the promotion meeting as a volunteer. She said: "The people in the hometown are the most close, the taste of the hometown is the most beautiful, and the brand of" Huanxiang People "evokes too much nostalgia and memories. It is the food of the time, I hope that the" Huanxiang People "brand will go further and further and further and bigger."
Dr. Tan Bin, a researcher at the Scientific Research Institute of the National Food and Material Reserve Bureau, said that through the detection of more than 900 sets of indicators, the testing data of buckwheat, bitter, black beans and other agricultural products in Huanxian County are outstanding, and the content of many physiological active substances in miscellaneous grains is higher than the standard data. "Huanxiang people" has the inherent advantage of grabbing the domestic high-end grain market.
Chai Chun, secretary of the county party committee of Huanxian County, said that through the release of the "Huanxiang People" brand, it can further enhance the quality, standardization and large-scale innovation and development level of Huanxian high-quality agricultural products, which is conducive to shaping the overall image of Huanxian's agricultural products and rapidly enhancing visibility, competitiveness and added value.
Canada's gross domestic product (GDP) grew by 0.2% in July compared with the previous month, which was higher than expected, causing the market to expect the Bank of Canada to raise interest rates next month.
If it does raise interest rates, this will be the fifth time that the central bank has raised interest rates in a little more than a year.
Analysts interviewed by Reuters had previously estimated an increase of 0.1%.
Statistics Canada said Friday that 12 of the 20 industries achieved growth.
The reason why the data is noteworthy is that the central bank predicted earlier this month that temporary factors may drag down the third-quarter GDP data.
Bank of Canada President Poloz promised Thursday that the central bank will continue to raise interest rates gradually and will pay close attention to economic data.
The Bank of Canada's next interest rate decision will be announced on October 24.
As the Canadian economy strengthens and the unemployment rate is close to a record low, the Bank of Canada has raised interest rates four times since July 2017.
Stephen Brown, a senior Canadian economist at Kaitou Macro, said that the GDP growth rate of the country's economy in the third quarter is expected to reach about 2%.
"This will be higher than the 1.5% expected by the Bank of Canada, which will be another reason for the Bank of Canada to raise interest rates next month," he said in a report.
Overnight index swaps showed that the market's estimate of the Bank of Canada's interest rate hike in October rose from 76.46% to 78.27%.
The first joint inspection of the Han River in 65 years
South korea\ 's defense ministry confirmed on the 5th that the two Koreas launched a joint inspection of the waters at the mouth of the hanjiang and linjinjiang rivers on the same day.
The initiative is a preliminary preparation for ensuring the free navigation of private vessels on both sides.
South korea\ 's defense ministry provided to the media on the same day, this is the first time since the signing of the korean war armistice agreement in 1953, the two sides conducted a joint inspection of the hanjiang estuary.
The ROK and the DPRK signed a military agreement in September this year, and agreed to jointly inspect the waters such as the mouth of the Han River in November to ensure environmental protection and tourism in the future.
In October, the ROK and the DPRK planned a joint inspection of the waters during the general level meeting.
On November 5, the joint inspection of inter-Korean waters was officially launched.
The joint delegation was composed of 20 members, including the Korean military and experts.
According to the South Korean Defense Ministry, during the inspection, personnel from both sides did not carry weapons and prohibited the use of words and deeds that stimulated each other.
"Because there is no military demarcation line near the mouth of the sea, the area has been an unexpected high-incidence area, but through joint inspection, it will become a new peaceful area in the future."
The waters jointly inspected by the ROK and the DPRK have a total length of about 70 kilometers and a total area of about 280 square kilometers.
South korea\ 's defense ministry said that the south korean side will send six research vessels to detect the depth of seawater, etc., to provide basic information for the safe navigation of the waters; after the completion of the investigation, it will provide navigation maps for private vessels.
The ROK and the DPRK held a summit meeting in Pyongyang in October 2007 and reached an agreement on the joint use of the mouth of the Han River and the Linjin River, but the follow-up negotiations were stranded due to the tense situation on the peninsula.
According to the military agreement signed by the ROK and the DPRK in September, in the future, the ships of the two sides need to inform each other in advance before sailing in the common waters.
BEIJING, Nov. 5, according to the website of the Chinese Embassy in Mongolia on the 4th, recently, Chinese citizens Guo Yuqin and Mao Runxin lost their connection during the tour in Mongolia.
It is understood that the two are members of the blue sky rescue team. On October 19th, the two contacted domestic friends and relatives, saying that they would immediately enter the mountains near Kusugur Lake and share the location through WeChat. Since then, they have lost contact and suspected that they have gone to no-man's land.
The Chinese Embassy in Mongolia has always attached great importance to the protection of the legitimate rights and interests and security of Chinese citizens in Mongolia, and attaches great importance to consular protection and assistance.
After learning that the above two tourists lost the news, the embassy immediately started the emergency plan, and strive to seize the golden rescue time and fully carry out the work.
The embassy maintained close communication with the family members of the parties, assisted the family members to immediately report the case to the Mongolian police, and provided the family members with a translation list to choose from.
The embassy first met with the head of the Mongolian Ministry of External Relations, the General Administration of Police and the General Administration of Emergency Situations to inform the relevant situation, and asked the Mongolian side to carry out search and rescue as soon as possible, and to maintain close communication with the Mongolian side throughout the search and rescue process to ensure timely grasp of the latest progress.
At the same time, the Embassy assisted the family members to issue notices in Mongolia, and extensively mobilized overseas Chinese and Chinese enterprises in Mongolia to actively participate in the search, providing effective clues, and provided relevant assistance to many blue sky rescue team members who went to Mongolia to assist in the rescue.
Under the strong promotion of the embassy, the Mongolian side sent a rescue team for the first time and promised to exempt the search and rescue fees.
The Mongolian Police General Administration and the General Emergency Department instructed the police and emergency departments of Kusugur Province to fully search and rescue.
As Kusugur Lake is located at the junction of northern Mongolia and Russia, it is remote, sparsely populated, and transportation and communication are extremely inconvenient. At present, Mongolia has entered a severe winter, and the temperature is as low as minus 20 degrees. The local police and emergency departments have overcome huge difficulties, almost all police forces have been mobilized, and local herdsmen have been mobilized to carry out carpet search and rescue through horse riding, walking, visiting herdsmen, etc.
At the same time, in view of the special situation of pastoral areas, the Mongolian side has been publishing notices through the broadcast cycle for many days.
Domestic blue sky rescue team related staff have also come to Mongolia and Mongolia to actively participate in the rescue.
The safety of the two disconnected personnel has always touched our hearts.
So far, the two have been disconnected for more than ten days, and the embassy has received some clues, but they have not found two people. At present, the search and rescue operation is still under intense.
The Embassy will always follow the principle of "people-oriented," continue to pay attention to this matter, promote the Mongolian side to continue to search and rescue, and provide maximum assistance to the families of the parties.
The Embassy appeals to compatriots and enterprises in Mongolia. If you know the relevant clues, please contact the Chinese Embassy in Mongolia for the first time.
